-- 
BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Industrial Production, Budget Balance Figures

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-31T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/brazil-daybook-industrial-production-budget-balance-figures.html
Industrial production  in  Brazil 
probably rose 0.7 percent in April from a year earlier after
falling 2.1 percent in March, according to the median estimate
in a Bloomberg survey of 27 economists. The country’s statistics
agency releases the figures at 9 a.m. local time.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  meets with governors of cities
involved in hosting the 2014 soccer  World Cup  at 3 p.m.
*Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  has internal meetings.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has meetings in
Brasilia.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Tulio Maciel, head of the central bank economic research
department, speaks to reporters in Brasilia on the country’s
budget balance figures for the month of April, at 11 a.m.
*Former central bank President Henrique Meirelles and
billionaire Eike Batista speak at the Rio Investors Day
conference in Rio de Janeiro.
*Brazil’s coffee producers, exporters and government officials
speak at a seminar in  Sao Paulo  about the outlook for production
and exports, starting at 8 a.m.
*C40 Sao Paulo Summitt, an international conference of mayors
and representatives of the world’s largest cities to discuss
climate issues begins in Sao Paulo.
*Brazil’s new secretary of agricultural policy Jose Carlos Vaz
to hold presser in Brazilia at 11 a.m.  ECONOMY:
*Industrial production at 9 a.m.
*Budget balance figures at 10:30 a.m.
*Net debt at 10:30 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*CSN (CSNA3 BZ) failed to reach an agreement with striking
workers at its Casa de Pedra iron-ore mine in a meeting.
*Gol (GOLL4 BZ) rose the most in a month on speculation Lan
Airlines may bid for a stake in the company.
*Petrobras (PETR4 BZ) started drilling a new well at the
BMS-8 block.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 0.5 percent to 63,953.93.
*The real was little changed at 1.5944 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
